Reserve Bank Governor, Lesetja Kganyago, says the VAT increase will add about 0.6% points to the headline inflation. He says the stronger Rand will cushion the impact of the hike in VAT on inflation. On Wednesday, Kganyago announced the bank's decision to reduce the repo rate by 25 basis points to 6.5%.Â 

The overly indebted South African households will get slight relief after the Reserve Bank cut interest rates by 25 basis points. That has taken the repo rate, at which the Reserve Bank lends to commercial banks to 6.5%. This has taken the prime rate to 10% with effect from Thursday. The combination of a firmer Rand and the expected stability prompted Wednesday's rate cut. Economist, Elize Kruger, says this will go a long way to relieving households:

